AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Howard says budget to pave way for rate cuts.RTRS-Howard says budget to pave way for rate cuts.Australian Prime Minister John Howard said on Tuesday the federal budget due to be announced later in the day would lay the foundation for further cuts in interest rates in the medium term.  "Through the fiscal restoration it (the budget) will lay the foundation in the medium term for further reductions in interest rates," Howard told parliament.  The Reserve Bank of Australia cut official interest rates by 50 basis points to 7.0 percent on July 31.Treasury Peter Costello is due to hand down the 1996/97 budget at 7.30 p.m. (0930 GMT) and is expected to announce cuts of at least A$4.0 billion as the first stage of bringing the budget back into balance by 1998/99.-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 373-1800